{63826=HATTIESBURG, Mississippi (Ticker) -- Marvin Young had an 
87-yard punt return in the fourth quarter as Southern
Mississippi took advantage of six turnovers to post a 23-6
Conference USA victory over Memphis.

The Golden Eagles (2-1, 1-0 C-USA) beat Memphis for the ninth
time in the last 10 meetings by recovering three fumbles and
registering three interceptions.

Young, who returned four punts for 124 yards, gave Southern
Mississippi a 16-6 lead midway through the fourth. He broke
several tackles at midfield and coasted in for the score.

Tim Blackwell gained 96 yards on the ground and capped the
scoring with a 38-yard TD run with 1:50 remaining.

DeAngelo Williams rushed for 158 yards on 28 carries for Memphis
while Danny Wimprine completed 16-of-35 passes for 182 yards.
But he had three interceptions, none more costly than the one he
threw early in the fourth on 3rd-and-goal from the inside the 5

Memphis (2-1, 0-1) gained 374 total yards off offense, but only
managed two field goals by Stephen Gostkowski in the first half.}
